Short run
change over 6 months to a year

Keynes key insight: Macro vs Micro
Demand and supply analysis
    - Price vs Quantity  2d plot
    - Demand: Downward sloping line
        - At high price, demand is low
        - At low price, demand is high
    - Supply curve: Producer's decision making 
    - equilibrium
    
    - demand shift 
        ex: hot day     ==> demand for ice scream increases ==> price and quantity increase
        ex: cold day    ==> demand for ice scream drops     ==> price and quantity decrease
        ==> Price increase on hit days, and decrease on cold days
    - supply shift
        A positive shift in the supply of a good would cause prices to decrease and the quantity to increase

!!! But why isn't price for EVERYTHING changing on a DAILY basis? 
    ==> PRICE RIGIDITY
    ==> AS if SUPPLY CURVE was flat 
        - Equilibrium doesn't adjust due to shift in demand
        - (i.e price of ice scream does not change ifunction of weather and on a daily basis)   
        - P stay the same, but Q sold changes       <-- in short term, P doesn't have as much information as Q does

!!! The difference between short and long run is price adjustment.
    ==> Keynes in General Theory of Employment, Interest, and Money
        - analysis of an economy in the short run

